NOTE: THIS IS NOT A BEGINNER`S COURSE. *You must possess solid handgun shooting/manipulation skills.

The Personal Protection In the Home course teaches defensive / tactical shooting skills which cannot be taught on a typical "box" range.

This intermediate level course enables experienced shooters to move to cover, shoot from behind barricades, develop and employ advanced Flash-Sight-Picture skills, and much more.

We cover mindset, legal issues, decision-making under pressure, and planning for the worst.

This course is designed around the use of the defensive pistol where standard marksmanship skills will not work, and will better enable you to survive a felonious attack whether in or outside of your home.

Topical areas include: 
1. Defensive Shooting / Rapid Engagement 
2. Defensive Handgun Skills 3. Firearms and the Law: Possession, Ownership, and the Use of Deadly Force
 4. Strategies for Preventing a Home Invasion 
5. Responding to a Violent Confrontation 
6. Handgun Considerations for Personal Defense 
7. Three hours of Range Shooting 

Students receive the NRA Guide to Personal Protection in the Home handbook (a $20 value included in the price) and intensive lessons of defensive shooting, issues of self-defense, and other strategies for protecting the home and family.

You will also receive feedback on your shooting exercises, and methods to take your skill sets to the next level.

You will earn a National Rifle Association (NRA) certificate upon successful completion of this course.

Our next PPITH Course is scheduled for February 15th, 2014. Seats are limited and this course normally fills up quickly, so reserve your seat now. For more information visit www.PatriotTAC.com, and be sure to like us on Facebook!

title: For Sale/Trade:  Pre Civil War 1856 Ames Heavy Cavalry Sword "Wristbreaker"
postcontent: The model 1840 saber, called the "wrist breaker", was was a relatively heavy cavalry saber, and as it was manufactured before the Civil War, it saw extensive use by both sides during the war. Standard features include a relatively straight wooden handle covered with leather and a wire grip, brass hilt has three branches, brass pommel cap and guard are unadorned, steel blade has flat back with narrow and wide fuller stopped at the ricasso, iron scabbard with iron mountings. Manufactured by Ames Manufacturing Company, Chicopee, Massachusetts. Marks on ricasso, "AMES MFG CO / CHICOPEE / MASS / 1856"(you can read AME- C then 156) the 8 is gone along with the letters after the C in Chicopee and S in Ames. and "US / JH" both are clear., additional inspector stamping on pommel, ADK and RHKW, the KW is double stamped??? The grip has leather wrap and wire intact, leather washer intact.Blade length 36in.  This sword is in beautiful condition and is the pride of my collection, but I'm into something else now. It is as I found it condition. The blade and brass has been cleaned at some point. There are a couple of nicks in the last half of the blade, indicating this saw some kind of action. The wrap and wire are all there and are tight. The scabbard in in great condition and looks to bear the JH initials also. There are not many of these in this shape that come up for sale, take advantage while you can.

title: For Sale:  HK91 Clone/Sar 8 Overstamp in SFV for FEG AK or .308
postcontent:
This is an early Greek HK91 clone make on HK tooling. This gun started out as a Sar 3 that was over-stamped with an 8, fitted with a thumbhole stock and had the threaded barrel covered with a sleeve to avoid the old Federal AWB ban.This was originally an exact clone of an HK91 and it remains as close as you can get in CA to a true HK91. This one has a true threaded barrel not seen on later Sar 8 imports. 

The gun comes with the original thumbhole stock, one rebuild kit (for a few more days only), an original box and manual. The standard HK stock and pistol grip are not included. The box is for a Sar 8 but doesn't match the serial number on this rifle. The gun clearly has been shot very little. 

Springfield still backs these guns in case there is ever an issue. Don't confuse this rifle with later Springfield Sar8 rifles built on very problematic aluminum receivers. 

Interested in a FEG AK47 (not an AMD),M1a match rifle and a sub-MOA, DPMS compatible factory built .308 (GAP) or upper or another preban/ban rifle.

title: For Sale:  RANGE BRASS WILL SHIP .223 38 Special .45 ACP .40 9MM .380
postcontent:
I have a variety of indoor range brass for sale. They have been fired and still have the primers. You will need to clean and deprime them yourself. I try to pick out pieces that are Berdan primed or are bent to the point that they cannot be reloaded. However, some of these may get into the bags. I add an extra 10 pieces for every 500 to ensure you have quality pieces. I hand count each bag and get rid of any aluminum or steel casings. They are all brass or nickel coated brass! These are mixed headstamp and the .45s have not been sorted for primer size. These can be fixed with a cheap pocket reamer. You will find a lot of Lake City and Remington in .223 as well as a 5.56 once in a while. In the pistol cartridges, the majority are blazers, remingtons, winchesters, and federals. There are also the military rounds (less than 1% of the rounds), aguila, hornady, cor-bon, and speer to name a few.

My current inventory is:
[9mm Luger] 4 bags @ 1k casings each ($40/bag) or ($75/2 bags)

The $7 box can take very small packages while the $14 and $18 boxes will be more common for most orders.
